      "blocks": {
        "heading_axLTnn": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "<p>Bunions</p>",
            "heading_size": "title-md",
            "heading_tag": "h2",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "text_LHGLnM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>A bunion is characterized by a prominent bump on the inside of the foot around the big toe joint, caused by a bone protruding towards the inside of the foot. As the big toe moves toward the smaller toes, it can end up resting under or over the second toe, leading to a condition known as overlapping toes.</p><p>Symptoms of bunions include inflammation, swelling, and soreness on the side surface of the big toe, often causing improper walking.</p>",
            "text_font": "body",
            "text_size": "subtext-md",
            "text_max_size": 32,
            "text_line_height": 1.6,
            "text_letter_spacing": 0,
