    "faq_zhAACx": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "question_XamVPH": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>Causes</strong>",
            "text": "<p>A bunion is a prominent bump on the inside of the foot around the big toe joint. Some of the symptoms of bunions include inflammation, swelling, soreness or pain in the bunion area. </p><p>Bunions are more common in women and often result from improper fitting footwear, such as tight, narrow dress shoes with a constrictive toe box.<br/><br/>Wearing shoes that squeeze the toes together can cause the first metatarsal bone to protrude, leading to the formation of a bunion.<br/><br/><br/><br/></p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_x9EPUx": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>Treatment and Prevention</strong>",
            "text": "<p><strong>GET STRETCHING EXERCISE GUIDE</strong><br/>Our Plantar Fasciitis Kit comes with an exercise guide that helps give you instructions on how to stretch the plantar fascia as well as the muscles and tendons surrounding the tissue. In turn it can help with reducing tension and putting you on the path towards pain relief. </p><p><strong>SHOP RECOMMENDED ORTHOTICS</strong><br/>Orthotics are suggested to support the arch, especially for individuals with flat feet.Orthotics can help limit the progression of bunion formation and provide relief from pain. If the problem persists, consult your foot doctor.</p><p><strong>SHOP RECOMMENDED SHOES</strong><br/>Conservative treatment for bunion pain involves wearing shoes that accommodate the deformity.Shoes with a wide toe box are recommended to reduce pressure on the bunion.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "question_XamVPH",
        "question_x9EPUx"
      ],
